{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #111: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. If $G$ is a graph let $h_G(n)$ be defined such that any subgraph of $G$ on $n$ vertices can be made bipartite after deleting at most $h_G(n)$ edges.\n\nWhat is the behaviour of $h_G(n)$? Is it true that $h_G(n)/n\\to \\infty$ for every graph $G$ with chromatic number $\\aleph_1$? Current best: In \\cite{Er81} Erd\\H{o}s conjectured that this can be improved to $\\ll n^{1+\\epsilon}$ for every $\\epsilon>0$. Prize: no. Tags: chromatic number, graph theory, set theory.","id":"vf_3138df5d0acefa68","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 111 (PR #3785) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3785.","id":"vf_eec3d67e752bf719","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/111.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_3138df5d0acefa68","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:111","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_eec3d67e752bf719","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:111","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_eec3d67e752bf719","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_3138df5d0acefa68","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc16db143","frontier_root":